Clean code is always appreciated. In JavaScript, you can adopt ES6 syntax to make your code cleaner.

### Use an object for update multiple states at the same time

<CodeBlock
  children="const [state, setState] = useState({
     gender: &#x22;&#x22;,
     name: &#x22;&#x22;,
     age: 23
  });

  const onClick = () => {
     setState((prevState) => ({
       ...prevState,
       age: prevState.age + 1,
       name: &#x22;John&#x22;,
       gender: 'male',
     }));
  };"
  language="jsx"
/>
